Dr '''Ian Gould''' is the Chancellor of the [[University of South Australia]] and a former Managing Director (Australia) of [[Rio Tinto Group]]. A geologist and mining professional for over 40 years, Gould held a number of diverse and senior positions in the Rio Tinto Group (formerly Conzinc RioTinto Australia) including Group Executive for Exploration and Group Executive Research & Development. He is also a former chair of [[uranium mining]] company, [[Toro Energy]]. He resigned from Toro in April 2009 following his appointment as Chancellor at the university the previous year.<ref>{{Cite book|title = Toro Energy Annual Report 2009|last = |first = |publisher = Toro Energy|year = 2009|isbn = |location = |pages = 4|url = http://www.toroenergy.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/TORO+Annual+Report+2009.pdf}}</ref> In 2000, Gould retired from his executive career as Managing Director of the Adelaide-based [[Normandy Mining|Normandy Mining Group]]. He has since held a number of non-executive directorships within the resources sector, and received several accolades for his commitment to the resources industry.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url = http://www.minerals.dmitre.sa.gov.au/home/resource_industry_development_board/members_of_the_ridb?SQ_DESIGN_NAME=printer_friendly|title = Members of the RIDB|date = 2014|accessdate = 2014-09-15|website = Department of State Development|publisher = Government of South Australia|last = |first = }}</ref>

== Board & committee membership ==
Gould has held positions on several industry-specific government advisory boards and committees. He has previously chaired the [[Resources Industry Development Board|South Australian Resources Industry Development Board]], and currently chairs the [[South Australian Minerals & Petroleum Expert Group]] (SAMPEG) and the CSIRO Mineral Resources Sector Advisory Committee.<ref name=":0" /> He holds a position on the South Australian Premier's Science and Research Council.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url = http://www.unisanet.unisa.edu.au/staff/Homepage.asp?Name=Ian.Gould|title = Dr Ian Gould AM|date = |accessdate = 2014-09-15|website = University of South Australia|publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> He also is the present chair of the St Andrew's Hospital board, Vice president of the [[Royal Flying Doctor Service of Australia|Royal Flying Doctor Service]] (RFDS) Central Operations<ref name=":0" /> and a former member of the [[Economic Development Board]] of South Australia.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.adelaidenow.com.au/news/south-australia/half-of-sas-economic-development-board-replaced-with-new-faces/story-fni6uo1m-1226923281033|title = Half of SA's Economic Development Board replaced with new faces|last = Wills|first = Daniel|date = 2014-09-20|work = |accessdate = 2014-09-15}}</ref>

== Honours ==
Gould is a fellow of the Academy of Technological Sciences and Engineering and a past president and fellow of the [[AusIMM]].<ref name=":0" /> He was awarded the AusIMM's highest honour, the Institute Medal in 2007.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.miningaustralia.com.au/news/the-ausimm-honors-high-achievers|title = The AusIMM honors high achievers|date = 2007-12-30|accessdate = 2014-09-15|website = Mining Australia|publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> Gould was awarded an [[Australian Medal]] (AM) in the [[2011 Queen's Birthday Honours (Australia)|2011 Queen's birthday honours]] for services to mining, education and the community.<ref name=":0" /> Gould was appointed Chancellor of the University of South Australia in 2008.

== Education ==
Gould is a graduate of [[Sydney Technical High School]] and the [[University of Sydney]]. He holds a Bachelor of Science with Honors (Geology) and a PhD (Geology) from the latter.<ref name=":1" />

